sequenceDiagram
    participant S as Scheduler / User / Agent
    participant API as FastAPI Service
    participant RE as Rules Executor
    participant DS as Data Source<br/>(Postgres dev · Redshift prod)
    participant DB as App Database<br/>(PostgreSQL)
    participant Agent as AI Agent<br/>(Claude)

    S->>API: Trigger rule run (all active rules, or specific rule id)
    API->>DB: Load active rules
    DB-->>API: Rules list

    loop For each rule
        API->>RE: Execute rule
        RE->>DS: Run rule SQL query
        DS-->>RE: Result rows (each row = one data error)
        RE->>DB: Insert rule_run record (status, count)
        RE->>DB: Insert rule_error records (jsonb row data)
    end

    API->>Agent: Request post-run analysis
    Agent->>DB: Query error counts, trends, prior summaries
    DB-->>Agent: Error data
    Agent->>DB: Upsert error_summary records (per rule, per date)

    opt Agent detects notable pattern or anomaly
        Agent->>DB: Write knowledge_entry (title, content, embedding)
    end

    API-->>S: Run complete — summary stats returned
